<mods:abstract>One of eight gates to the ancient city of Babylon. Materials from the excavation were brought to Berlin
    and the gate reconstructed, completed in 1930, for display in the Pergamon Museum. Considered a major object 
    of the cultural heritage by modern day Iraqis, many advocate for the return of the gate to their country.</mods:abstract>
